Here is the commit message:
Modify SpEL code gen to take account of null safe refs

With this change the code generation for method and property
references is modified to include branching logic in the
case of null safe dereferencing (?.). This is complicated
by the possible usage of primitives on the left hand side
of the dereference. To cope with this case primitives are
promoted to boxed types when this situation occurs enabling
null to be passed as a possible result.

Issue: SPR-16489

Here is the root cause:
The bug was caused by the lack of proper handling for null-safe dereferencing in the code generation for method and property references. Specifically, when a null-safe operator (?.) was used, the code did not account for the possibility of primitives being dereferenced, which could lead to type errors or unexpected behavior when null values were encountered. The modifications introduced branching logic to handle these cases correctly by promoting primitives to their boxed types when necessary.

